In article <2kefj2$47@usenet.INS.CWRU.Edu> dr261@cleveland.Freenet.Edu (Tobin T Fricke) writes:
> Tempest for T.V?  In Ireland, you need a "Television License" to
> operate a T.V.  They (the police) have a van with some type of
> device which can detect whether or not a T.V. is operating at
> a specific place of residence.  I doubt if the device can 
> actually find out what you are watching

It can - it detects leakage from one of the IF transformers in your set,
and so the recovered signal can just be displayed on a set inside the
van.

